  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">COVID 19 and Flood Response in Bihar- 2020</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">By infusing cash into the local/mico economy, it will not only help address the immediate needs of these marginalized households but also boost the health of the local vendors and businesses.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To improve on our efforts to link beneficiaries to existing support systems, the project will identify the households that have the least coping capacity, are the worst affected due to COVID 19 and subsequently with floods this year in Bihar and in need of immediate support in the form of financial assistance and by helping the target community gain access to social security schemes. Subsequently, these households will be aided by us with the help of Unconditional Cash Transfers (UCT) that will help them cope and meet critical needs. Ground reports have suggested the provisional opening of local markets to serve the community, the project will engage the community and help them leverage this to their benefit.</narrative>
  </description>
